    "causal_summary": "Phase 001 is a new prerequisite planning packet for replacing the current partial mcp-coco-index soft fork with a complete local fork of the upstream cocoindex-code MCP wrapper at v0.2.33. Research found the local fork is still labeled 0.2.3+spec-kit-fork.0.2.0 and carries a narrow patch overlay, while upstream v0.2.33 has a broader package, tests, runtime path helpers, Docker assets, and CLI/doctor surface. This phase keeps the transitive cocoindex engine as a pinned external dependency unless scope expands, then ports current spec-kit search telemetry and ranking patches onto the full wrapper baseline.",
